# Package installation

## From this GitHub repository
Clone the following repo:
```bash
git clone path_to_repo
cd atommap_eval
```

Create an `atommap-eval` environment:
```bash
conda create -n atommap-eval python=3.9
conda activate atommap-eval
```

Install required packages with conda:
```bash
conda install -c conda-forge rdkit networkx pandas
```

Then from the root of the folder:
```bash
pip install -e .
```

Or in dev mode to have the pytest installed as well:
```bash
pip install -e .[dev]
```
